Elias Elias
2:27 PM (0 minutes ago)
to me

It was running super rough and clanking noise and won’t speed up at all. It came in on a tow truck we took the coil pack off and removed the spark plugs. Noticed the tips of the number 1 and 2 plugs where melted/ broken right off. 3 and 4 plugs where fine. Did a compression test on all cylinders found that 3 and 4 had 150 psi each. Cylinders  1 and 2 on the other hand had 0 psi. So we took the valve cover off to inspect the cams didn’t see anything with the timing belt or cam shafts. Tried to visually inspect the guides and springs for the valves but couldn’t really see anything obviously broken.
